<SLUG> BC-BKN-NOTEBOOK-YOUNG-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JACKSON, LAKERS MAY GET TOGETHER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are few nicer men in the NBA than former Lakers Coach  &UR; Del
 &UR; Harris, who got the ax last week after 12 games.
</P>
<P>
   But it came as little surprise. In fact, many expected the move
to come after the Lakers lost an overtime game to Denver. Several
NBA scouts working that game noticed that the Lakers bench was
lifeless, even when LA made a big rally that forced overtime.
</P>
<P>
   It was a sign that the Lakers had quit responding to Harris, but
owner  &UR; Jerry Buss and General Manager  &UR; Jerry West gave Harris
another game. When the Lakers lost to Vancouver, there was little
doubt about what would happen next.
</P>
<P>
   ``The only thing you can do in LA is win, that's it,'' Miami
Coach
 &UR; Pat Riley told reporters covering the Heat. Riley spent nine years
as Lakers coach, played there and worked as an analyst on club
broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
   Already, speculation has begun about former Chicago Coach  &UR; Phil
 &UR; Jackson taking over.  &UR; Kurt Rambis has the job on an interim basis.
His performance will be evaluated at season's end. There is little
doubt that Jackson will be interested.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Lakers have not contacted us at this point, Jackson's
agent,
 &UR; Todd Musburger, told the ``Chicago Sun-Times'' last week. ``We
cannot rule out (his coaching) this season. But we should not read
too much into that because we are in hypothetical land, and Phil is
quite happy working the speaking tour.''
</P>
<P>
   Of course, Musburger pointed out that he included ``cancellation
provisions'' in contracts that Jackson has for speaking
engagements. But with Rambis in place, those won't be necessary
unless Jackson goes to another team later this season.
</P>
<P>
   It makes plenty of sense. Jackson knows how to deal with  &UR; Dennis
 &UR; Rodman, assuming Rodman returns next season. He has shown he can
handle a superstar such as  &UR; Shaquille O'Neal, coaching the  &UR; Michael
 &UR; Jordan-led Bulls to six championships.
</P>
<P>
   But there also has been speculation that Jackson, who has a home
in Montana, might prefer a more laid-back atmosphere and wind up in
Denver, where the Nuggets have given Coach  &UR; Mike D'Antoni only a
one-year commitment.
</P>
<P>
   Ultimately, it will be Jackson's call. Apparently, there is no
lack of opportunity for the Zen Master. Musburger said a half-dozen
NBA teams already have inquired about his availability. &QL; 
Say what? &QL; 
Orlando Coach  &UR; Chuck Daly recently told reporters who cover the
Magic that he finds the Sacramento Kings to be a team capable of
capturing the imagination of fans during a season in which scoring
is at a premium.
</P>
<P>
   ``They have easily, I think, the most entertaining team in
basketball,'' Daly said. ``They run the ball. They've got post-up
people. They are not a team that you particularly like to play very
often. I think NBC and TNT are missing out on something very
entertaining.''
</P>
<P>
   We couldn't agree more, especially with the flair that rookie
 &UR; Jason
 &UR; Williams brings to the game. But isn't this the same Chuck Daly who
brought us the Bad Boy Detroit Pistons, who started the whole
bump-and-grind routine that has stifled scoring? &QL; 
Not so fast &QL; 
Reports that clauses in  &UR; Jason Kidd's contract could allow him to
become a free agent at the end of next season may not be complete,
says a source familiar with Phoenix guard's contract.
</P>
<P>
   While language in the contract relates to what are known as
early termination options _ in Kidd's case, based on criteria tied
to individual statistics and the number of team victories _ a
stipulation in the contract supersedes those clauses, the source
said. It apparently is not as simple as meeting incentives.
</P>
<P>
   Suns General Manager  &UR; Bryan Colangelo would not comment on the
contract or the reports, other than to say, ``Whatever the
circumstances are regarding Jason's contract, we anticipate him
being a part of this team for a long time.''
</P>
<P>
   Kidd is signed through the 2002-2003 season. If he became a free
agent at the end of next season with six years in the NBA, Kidd
would be eligible to receive a new seven-year deal from Phoenix
that would start at 25 percent of the salary cap, but not less than
$9 million for the first season of the new pact. &QL; 
Trivia &QL; 
Brothers  &UR; Dominique and  &UR; Gerald Wilkins are playing together for
the first time in their careers this season in Orlando. Who were
the first brothers to play together on an NBA team? &QL; 
Hard hat area &QL; 
Seattle's  &UR; Vin Baker, a career 63.4 percent free throw shooter in
the NBA, had made only four of his 33 attempts from the line
through Thursday's games, or 12.1 percent. He's on a strong pace to
supplant &UR; Chris Dudley's 31.9 percent free throw shooting in 1989-90
as the worst on record. &QL; 
On second thought &QL; 
Philadelphia Coach  &UR; Larry Brown was asked in a recent television
interview whether he believes his 76ers are a playoff team.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think so,'' Brown answered.
</P>
<P>
   This prompted a number of telephone calls, including one from
club President  &UR; Pat Croce.
</P>
<P>
   ``When asked, I meant the playoffs shouldn't be a given,'' Brown
said. ``I don't say that (they can't make it) in the locker room. I
tell them, if we're playing, we might as well try and win the
championship. I told Pat there's no one in our locker room who
doesn't think I think we can make the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   Trivia answer &QL; 
If you guessed  &UR; Dick and  &UR; Tom Van Arsdale of the Suns, try again.
The Van Arsdales were teammates in 1976-77 for the Suns. But  &UR; Dick
and  &UR; Al &UR; McGuire were New York Knicks teammates from 1951-54. &QL; 
Includes information from other media sources. Bob Young can be
reached at 602-444-8271 or at bob.young(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
