Germany's citizenship law and its intention to reduce the country's
dependence on nuclear energy, the Schroder government is off to a
bumpy start. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   FISHING-CUTBACKS (Washington) _ For the first time, the world's
nations are moving toward comprehensive reductions in the bloated
global fishing fleet that experts say has brought many of the
world's fish stocks to the brink of collapse. By John H. Cushman.
