<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-28 16:44 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2285 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     02-28 0726
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c. 1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; HOTEL SUITE NAMED AFTER THE COMMUNICATOR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In Los Angeles, the Century Plaza Hotel and Tower has renamed
its 30th floor the  &UR; Ronald Reagan &LR;  Suite, and you can drop on in
for a sleepover for $5,400 a night.
</P>
<P>
   There's even a local angle: The theme for the suite was executed
by San Francisco designer  &UR; Bennett Hall &LR; , who collected and curated
images from what the brochure calls the ``Reagan legacy'' and
selected memorabilia and knickknacks to convey the greatness of the
former president. Among the suite's amenities:
</P>
<P>
   Bullet-proof glass windows; a library of Reagan-connected books,
including ``The Uncommon Wisdom of Ronald Reagan''; a video library
that includes ``Bedtime for Bonzo'' and ``Brother Rat''; and a jar
of jelly beans.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FAMILY AFFAIRS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Popeye  &LR; and  &UR; Olive Oyl &LR;  get married in a comic released last
week. ``So we're finally hitched!'' says Popeye after the ceremony.
``Well, blow me down!''
</P>
<P>
   To which the saucy Olive Oyl replies, ``Later, Popeye, later.''
_ In the forthcoming movie ``Duets,''  &UR; Angie Dickinson &LR;  plays
 &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; 's grandmother, says Variety, and  &UR; Huey &LR; 
 &UR; Lewis &LR;  plays Paltrow's father.
</P>
<P>
   _ A SOMA review of O (set down) 2, the Los Angeles restaurant
owned by actor  &UR; Woody Harrelson  &LR; and his wife,  &UR; Lisa &LR; , describes it
as an oxygen bar and raw foods restaurant that serves only
nonalcoholic herbal cocktails and closes at 4 a.m. on weekends. So
it's a place for the pure of heart whose only vice is staying up
late.
</P>
<P>
   - Helicopter pilot  &UR; Robert Butler  &LR; has been changed with
reckless flying and disturbing the peace for allegedly flying too
low over &UR; Barbra Streisand  &LR; and  &UR; James Brolin &LR; 's wedding July 1.
Deputy District Attorney  &UR; Martin Herscovitz &LR;  told the L.A. Times it
was the first time criminal charges have been filed against flying
paparazzi.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DRESSES THAT EARNED THE SPOTLIGHT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   On March 18, three days before the Oscars are awarded,
Christie's will auction dresses worn to past Academy Awards
ceremonies. The sale of 54 gowns will benefit the American
Foundation for AIDS research.
</P>
<P>
   There's no minimum bid, but  &UR; Nancy Valentino  &LR; of Christie's told
the New York Times that ``the jumping-off point will be $2,000.''
</P>
<P>
   Among those expected to fetch the highest prices: a blue and
violet dress designed by  &UR; Edith Head  &LR; for  &UR; Elizabeth Taylor  &LR; to
wear in 1969 and a silk dress that  &UR; Lauren Bacall  &LR; wore in 1978.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
