<P>
   &UR; HOTEL SUITE NAMED AFTER THE COMMUNICATOR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In Los Angeles, the Century Plaza Hotel and Tower has renamed
its 30th floor the  &UR; Ronald Reagan &LR;  Suite, and you can drop on in
for a sleepover for $5,400 a night.
</P>
<P>
   There's even a local angle: The theme for the suite was executed
by San Francisco designer  &UR; Bennett Hall &LR; , who collected and curated
images from what the brochure calls the ``Reagan legacy'' and
selected memorabilia and knickknacks to convey the greatness of the
former president. Among the suite's amenities:
</P>
<P>
   Bullet-proof glass windows; a library of Reagan-connected books,
including ``The Uncommon Wisdom of Ronald Reagan''; a video library
that includes ``Bedtime for Bonzo'' and ``Brother Rat''; and a jar
of jelly beans.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FAMILY AFFAIRS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Popeye  &LR; and  &UR; Olive Oyl &LR;  get married in a comic released last
week. ``So we're finally hitched!'' says Popeye after the ceremony.
``Well, blow me down!''
</P>
<P>
   To which the saucy Olive Oyl replies, ``Later, Popeye, later.''
_ In the forthcoming movie ``Duets,''  &UR; Angie Dickinson &LR;  plays
 &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; 's grandmother, says Variety, and  &UR; Huey &LR; 
 &UR; Lewis &LR;  plays Paltrow's father.
</P>
