<P>
   KOREA-MISSILES (Undated) _ It was just a brief comment by the
chairman of the House International Relations Committee, but it was
enough to make Northwesterners sit up and take note. ``For 40
years, North Korea posed a threat to 37,000 American troops and the
South Korean capital of Seoul,'' Rep. Benjamin Gilman, R-N.Y., told
his committee Thursday. ``Now they are threatening our mainland. In
short, we must now worry about our safety in Seattle, not just
Seoul.'' Gilman was referring to reports by U.S. and Japanese
defense experts that North Korea now has the technology to launch a
long-range ballistic missile capable of reaching the northwest
coast of the United States.
</P>
