<HEADER>
A2352 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT &LR;      02-28 0455
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
U.S. TO AUCTION DEBT TWO DAYS THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The words PLUS and MINUS in parentheses have been used
instead of the symbols, which are non-transmittable to many
newspaper systems.) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week offers Monday's
regular weekly auction of new three- and six-month bills, as well
as a 52-week bill and a 12-day cash management bill that will be
auctioned Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   According to traders, at the close of the New York cash market
on Friday the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was at 4.54
percent and the rate on the six-month issue was 4.53 percent. The
rate for the 52-week bill was 4.62 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following tax-exempt fixed-income issues are scheduled for
pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Computer Sciences Corp., $200 million of notes due in 2009,
A2/A/---/. J.P. Morgan Securities.
</P>
<P>
   Group One Automotive Inc., $100 million of senior subordinate
notes due in 2009, B2/B/---/. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Standard Pacific Corp., $100 million of senior subordinate notes
due in 2009, B1/B(PLUS)/---/. Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette.
</P>
<P>
   Suncor Energy Inc., 6 million shares of $25 preferred due in
2048, Baa1/BBB(MINUS)/---/. Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM Corporatewatch
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Moody's Investors Service/Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp./Duff
&AMP; Phelps Credit.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
