<HEADLINE>
USC, NIT SEPARATED BY TWO DESERT VICTORIES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has not won at Arizona since 1985, but the
Trojans will probably need an upset at McKale Center on Thursday
for any chance of making the National Invitation Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``The road is tough, but we've been in some road games,'' USC
coach Henry Bibby said. ``I'm happy going into the Arizona and
Arizona State games. Both of those teams are beatable. But we can't
have any lulls in our game there. We have to play consistent on
both ends of the floor.''
</P>
<P>
   The daunting scenario for the Trojans (14-11, 6-10) is that even
if they somehow buck the odds and defeat the seventh-ranked
Wildcats, they probably also have to beat Arizona State in Tempe on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't beat Arizona and then not beat Arizona State,'' USC
center Brian Scalabrine said. ``That won't really help us.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Improved defense: USC's defense continues to improve. The
Trojans have held opposing teams to 43 percent shooting or less in
the past seven games and given up 68 points or less in six of
those.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we understand now that Bibby has a lot of concepts,''
Scalabrine said. ``Now guys are starting to understand where and
when to play defense, when to play man-to-man and when to play
zone.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Better intensity: USC is now 4-5 in the second half of Pac-10
play, not exactly impressive but far better than the Trojans' 2-7
record in the first round of conference games. What's the
difference?
</P>
<P>
   ``We're more experienced and focused on what we have to do,''
freshman forward Sam Clancy said. ``In the beginning, I feel we
were going through the motions.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Subtle stat: USC sophomore center Greg Lakey has quietly put
together an impressive streak. Lakey has made 17 straight free
throws and is shooting 87 percent for the season, well above last
season's average of 53 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
