<HEADLINE>
CSUN COACH TO DECIDE PLAYERS' FATE TODAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ Cal State Northridge men's basketball coach Bobby
Braswell will meet with suspended players Greg Minor and Rico
Harris today to determine the players' fate for the Big Sky
Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Minor, a junior guard, and Harris, a junior forward, were
suspended prior to the Matadors' trip to Weber State and Sacramento
State for what Braswell termed ``conduct detrimental to the team.''
</P>
<P>
   The Matadors went 1-1 on the trip and finished 9-7 in the Big
Sky Conference, 17-11 overall. They open the conference tournament
Thursday against Montana State.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell suspended five players last year. Minor, CSUN's top
3-point shooter, and Harris, the team's top rebounder, were the
first suspensions this season.
</P>
</TEXT>
