<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-28 23:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2643 &Cx1f; tth-z
r v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-1ST-LEDE-SPI &LR;      02-28 0135
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-1ST-LEDE-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the additional
story for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, March 1 and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-NORTHWEST (Seattle) _ Vice President Al Gore predicted here
Sunday that the government will deal successfully with any Year
2000 computer glitches before the new milennium. In a wide-ranging
interview, he indicated the Clinton administration will work to
keep a rescue tugboat at the mouth of the Strait of Juan de Fuca
and said the White House soon will appoint a special envoy in a
renewed effort to resolve the long-running U.S.-Canada salmon
dispute.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``w'' file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
